  "text": "Previous work (e.g. [CITATION_1] has shown that exclusion effort can often be reduced by using controls that vary in time. How much reduction is achievable is found from the minimum exclusion effort (E*) given by the solution of the optimal control problem (9) below. This allows us to compare minimum effort E* (for a varying control) with effort E0 (for a constant control) and hence with R0 (the basic reproduction number).",
